title: Machine Learning Research
description: Worked with animal science researchers from Cornell University's Lei Lab to train predictive AI on the nutritional outcomes of broiler chickens. This project encompassed the entire length of model development, from assembling a database of various diets to model selection, training, and evaluation. Finally, model interpretation was performed to search for new insights and inform the future direction of research.

title: Design Build Fly Project Team
description: Cornell University's Design Build Fly project team is a student-run organization in which members develop, build, test, and optimize a custom radio-controlled aircraft to compete in the international DBF competition. The competition, sponsored by Textron Aviation, Raytheon, and the American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics, enables students to engage in the design process and to produce an aircraft that meets the requirements of a specified mission profile.

title: WebSync
description: This project involved the development of a website that would allow users to compare similar pieces of web fiction. The backend of this website involved creating a searchable database of matches between the descriptions and tags of various pieces, while a custom user interface was created and styled for the frontend.

title: SQL From Scratch
description: Created for a databases practicum, this project involved writing a database system from scratch in Java. The system was required to support basic SQL operations such as SELECT, FROM, ORDER BY, and JOIN, and was capable of parsing and executing those commands.
